Class ClientSideExample

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.components.AbstractComponent
      • fr.sorbonne_u.components.plugins.dconnection.example.components.ClientSideExample
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComponentI

    public class ClientSideExample
extends AbstractComponent
    The class ClientSideExample shows how a client component can use the dynamic connection plug-in to connect itself with a server component and call its services.

    Description

    To benefit from the example, carefully read the code and adapt it to your needs in your own code.

    Invariant

     invariant              true

    Created on : 2017-02-17

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public void execute()
             throws java.lang.Exception
        Description copied from interface: ComponentI
        execute a task on the component after all components have been started; this method is automatically called by the component virtual machine after all components have been started and the component calls in turn its own inner components. Implementations of this method can keep the control as long as they wish (contrary to start) but they need to begin by a call to super if inner components also have an execute method to be called; it is the responsibility of programmers to make sure that this does not provoke deadlocks.

        Contract

         pre    this.isStarted()
 post   true                    // no postcondition.
